<HEADLINE> German Air Force Investigates Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOLLOMAN AIR FORCE BASE, N.M. (AP) -- Six German air force  
representatives have begun investigating the crash of two warplanes 
that apparently collided during a training mission. 
</P>
<P>
	The European-made Tornado planes went down during a training  
mission last Friday. They had taken off from a German flight 
training center at Holloman Air Force Base, about 100 miles 
northwest of the crash site. 
</P>
<P>
	The investigators visited the crash site Tuesday.  
</P>
<P>
	The four German air force crew members -- an instructor and  
student pilot in each plane -- parachuted to safety onto a ranch 
near Carlsbad. Two returned to Holloman earlier this week after 
treatment in Carlsbad. The other two were discharged Tuesday after 
treatment in Alamogordo. 
</P>
<P>
	The German air force training center at Holloman has about 580  
military personnel and 25 Tornado planes. 
</P>
