<HEADLINE> Fleet,BankBoston Offer New Benefits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Fleet and BankBoston will offer health benefits to  
the unmarried domestic partners of their 50,000 employees following 
completion of their merger, the two banks announced Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The extended family benefit will give employees the option of  
including a parent or other dependent relative on their insurance 
plan, as well as an unmarried domestic partner of the same or 
opposite sex. 
</P>
<P>
	The policy has been in effect at BankBoston since July 1998, and  
it will be extended to all eligible employees of the combined bank 
beginning in April. 
</P>
<P>
	Other elements of the benefits package include $5,000 in  
assistance to parents hoping to adopt children, and two paid days 
off each year for employees to participate in community volunteer 
programs. 
</P>
<P>
	The banks' merger would create the nation's eighth-largest bank.  
It awaits approval from state regulators. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
