<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  McGwire Leads Home Run Race With 63 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Mark McGwire regained the major league home run  
lead for the first time since Aug. 18, hitting Nos. 62 and 63 
Wednesday night in a doubleheader against the San Diego Padres. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire hit a homer in each game to move one ahead of Chicago's  
Sammy Sosa. McGwire last led Sosa 48-47. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire has 520 career homers, leaving him one behind Ted  
Williams and Willie McCovey for 10th place on the all-time list. He 
also leads the NL with 145 RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire tied Sosa for the major league lead in the fourth inning  
of the opener with a two-run homer to center that traveled an 
estimated 462 feet. He sent a 1-0 pitch from Matt Clement well over 
the wall as the ball cleared an area of shrubbery just beneath the 
backdrop. 
</P>
<P>
	Center fielder Ruben Rivera threw it back over the wall, leading  
to a scramble for the ball. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire hit a three-run homer off Andy Ashby, who surrendered  
Nos. 500 and 501 on Aug. 5 in St. Louis, in the sixth inning of the 
second game. The 467-foot shot also easily cleared the center-field 
wall and landed beyond the shrubbery. It bounced back onto the 
field and center fielder Mike Darr tossed it back in the stands. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
