<HEADLINE> McGwire Hits 62nd Home Run </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Mark McGwire tied Sammy Sosa for the major  
league home-run lead, hitting his 62nd Wednesday in the fourth 
inning of a doubleheader opener against San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire hit a 1-0 pitch from Matt Clement over the center-field  
wall for a two-run homer, a drive estimated at 462 feet. The ball 
cleared the shrubbery beyond the wall, then bounced back onto the 
field. Center fielder Ruben Rivera threw it back over the wall, 
leading to a scramble for the ball. 
</P>
<P>
	The home run was the 519th of McGwire's career and his second in  
three days, leaving him two behind Ted Williams and Willie McCovey, 
who are tied for 10th place. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire has an NL-leading 142 RBIs.  
</P>
<P>
	The homer was witnessed by the smallest home crowd since McGwire  
joined the Cardinals in 1997. Tuesday night's game was rained out 
and rescheduled as a doubleheader Wednesday. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
