<HEADLINE> Gagner Retires From Hockey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- Dave Gagner, who played for six teams during his  
15-year NHL career, announced his retirement Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm very fortunate to have made a living playing the game I  
love,'' Gagner said in a statement. ``At this time, I would like to 
spend more time with my family and pursue other interests.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The 34-year-old unrestricted free agent played for the New York  
Rangers, Minnesota North Stars-Dallas Stars, Toronto Maple Leafs, 
Calgary Flames, Florida Panthers and Vancouver Canucks. 
</P>
<P>
	In 946 NHL games, he scored 318 goals and finished with 719  
points. He played the last 33 games with the Canucks and scored two 
goals. 
  	   	
</P>
