<HEADLINE> Yields Rise in T-Note Auction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Yields on two-year Treasury notes rose in  
Wednesday's auction to the highest level in three months. 
</P>
<P>
	The yield was 5.665 percent, up from 5.557 percent at the last  
auction on Aug. 25. It was the highest rate since two-year notes 
sold for 5.754 percent on June 23. 
</P>
<P>
	The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 5 5/8 percent with  
each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,992.50. 
</P>
<P>
	A total of $15 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling  
$31.5 billion. 
  	   	
</P>
