<HEADLINE> Six Bodies Found in Alabama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ENTERPRISE, Ala. (AP) -- A muddy 1989 Chevrolet Caprice with six  
bodies inside was pulled from the Pea River on Wednesday, ending a 
mystery that began in May when a group of friends disappeared after 
a night of partying. 
</P>
<P>
	The vehicle's license plate matched the missing Caprice  
belonging to Lamar Junior Stackhouse, 25, of Enterprise. It was 
discovered Wednesday afternoon by authorities still following the 
case. 
</P>
<P>
	Autopsies were planned to determine how the six died, though  
investigators said the damage indicated the car ran off a bridge 
and crashed into the river. 
</P>
<P>
	Stackhouse and his friends, all in their 20s, disappeared after  
leaving a nightclub May 9. Investigators said they had found no 
evidence of foul play. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
