<HEADLINE> 38 Hurt in School Bus Crash in Ohio </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SOUTH BLOOMFIELD, Ohio (AP) -- A school bus carrying  
seventh-graders on a field trip flipped over on the side of a rural 
highway on Wednesday, injuring 38 students. 
</P>
<P>
	The bus apparently slipped off the shoulder of the narrow  
two-lane road, and the driver overcorrected, Pickaway County 
Sheriff's Lt. J. Phillip Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
	Most of the injured students and the driver had bumps and  
bruises. One child with a shoulder injury was in fair condition. 
</P>
<P>
	Superintendent Ron Thornton said the students were on an annual  
field trip to the Ohio Renaissance Festival. 
</P>
<P>
	``We feel very fortunate that it wasn't worse,'' he said.  
``Thank God for that.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In Columbus, a bus carrying elementary school students was hit  
by a car turning in front of an oncoming truck. Six pupils on the 
bus and a driver in another vehicle were treated for 
non-life-threatening injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	And in Minneapolis, two school buses crashed into each other  
Wednesday morning when one was traveling the wrong direction down a 
one-way street. The 17 children and three adults on the two buses 
were treated at a hospital and released. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
