<P>
	Stocks Close Lower; Dow Down 62.05  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks turned lower at the close of trading  
today, breaking out of a tight range as investors worried about 
interest rates and corporate earnings. The Dow Jones industrial 
average closed down 62.05 at 10,213.48. Broader stock indicators 
also ended lower. The Nasdaq composite index fell 22.16 to 
2,734.09. Concerns that the Fed will raise rates for the third time 
this year have contributed to a steep decline in the stock market 
this month. Stocks were also hurt by the latest round of corporate 
profit warnings. Gillette said late yesterday that third-quarter 
sales will be about 1 percent below last year's levels, prompting a 
number of downgrades from Wall Street analysts. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
Dow Industrials:        10,213.48  - 62.05
NYSE Issues:         Advances 1,599  Declines 1,440  Unchgd  510
