<HEADLINE> Lakers' Fox Weds Vanessa Williams </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Rick Fox, a star athlete whose rugged good  
looks opened the door to acting opportunities, and Vanessa L. 
Williams, a deposed Miss America who later found fame in the 
entertainment field, have married. 
</P>
<P>
	Fox, who signed a six-year, $24 million contract with the Los  
Angeles Lakers last month, and Williams, a Grammy Award-winning 
singer who has starred in several movies, were wed last Sunday in 
New York. 
</P>
<P>
	About 55 guests made up of family and close friends attended the  
ceremony at the Holy Trinity Church, according to Douglas Johnson, 
Fox's business manager. A reception followed at the St. Regis 
Hotel. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was a very beautiful and wonderful ceremony,'' Johnson  
said, adding that no Lakers and no entertainers attended. 
</P>
<P>
	Fox, 30, has a 5-year-old son, Kyle, while Williams, 36, has  
three children from a previous marriage. 
</P>
<P>
	Fox, who appeared in the movie ``He Got Game'' as well as the  
HBO series ``Oz,'' begins training camp with the Lakers next week. 
Williams is currently filming a remake of the movie ``Shaft,'' 
starring Samuel L. Jackson. 
</P>
<P>
	Williams was selected Miss America in 1984, but forced to resign  
after nude pictures of her appeared in Penthouse magazine during 
her reign. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
