<HEADLINE> Boy Sentenced in Fla. Dragging Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- A 15-year-old boy who was in the  
back seat of a stolen car when his buddy hit the gas and ran over 
an elderly woman, dragging her to death, has cut a deal to stay out 
of prison. 
</P>
<P>
	Martroy Futch will spend the next six to eight months in a  
juvenile detention center after pleading guilty Tuesday to being an 
accessory after the fact in the purse-snatching and death of Ida 
Mirel. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Mirel, 84, was killed when she tried to get back her purse  
from two boys in the parking lot of a Boca Raton restaurant. The 
boys in the stolen 1991 Dodge ran her over and dragged her body 
2,000 feet down a busy road. 
</P>
<P>
	Futch was charged in August with trying to wipe fingerprints off  
the car and helping to push it into a canal. If he had been charged 
as an adult with the same felony, he could have faced 30 years in 
prison. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities say Futch will testify in the trial of two other  
boys charged with murder in the May 8 attack. They face life in 
prison if convicted. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
