<HEADLINE> 3Com, Microsoft Ship Home Net Kit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SANTA CLARA, Calif. (AP) -- 3Com Corp. and Microsoft Corp. this  
week began shipping a home network kit that allows consumers to 
link home computers and printers in different rooms. 
</P>
<P>
	The HomeConnect kit uses Ethernet network cables to link  
computers, printers and scanners to a network hub device, allowing 
the sharing of files and multi-player video game playing. 
</P>
<P>
	The home network kits use Microsoft's HomeClick Network Software  
to simplify installation, the companies said Wednesday in a 
statement. 
</P>
<P>
	3Com and Microsoft reached an agreement in March to create the  
networking kit, which is similar to the Ethernet product 3Com 
provides for small businesses. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
