<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rockets Sign Shandon Anderson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	The Houston Rockets have signed free agent shooting guard  
Shandon Anderson, who left the Utah Jazz. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms of the deal were not disclosed in the team announcement  
today, but a a league source with knowledge of the negotiations, 
speaking on the condition of anonymity, told the Associated Press 
that the Rockets had offered Anderson a two-year, $4.2 million 
contract. 
</P>
<P>
	Anderson had told the Jazz that he preferred to sign elsewhere.  
The Indiana Pacers were the only other team offering Anderson a 
similar deal. 
</P>
<P>
	The offer, including a player option for a third year at $2.4  
million, is the most the Rockets can give Anderson because the club 
is over the $34 million salary cap for the upcoming season. 
</P>
<P>
	The 25-year-old Anderson has played his entire three-year career  
in Utah, averaging 7.6 points a game. Last week, Jazz owner Larry 
Miller said the team was had been told by Anderson that he wanted a 
change, in part because of he preferred a more urban setting that 
Salt Lake City. 
</P>
<P>
	Utah also said it would refuse to make a sign-and-trade deal,  
which would bring them something in return for Anderson. 
</P>
<P>
	The Jazz had offered Anderson more that $3 million per season  
and a guaranteed spot in the starting lineup. 
</P>
<P>
	With the Rockets, he would play alongside rookie Steve Francis  
in the backcourt. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
