<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Wednesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Tyson Foods, up 15/16 at 15 15/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Smithfield Foods is acquiring Tyson's hog production operations,  
Pork Group Inc., for about $80 million in stock. The deal is 
expected to allow Tyson to focus primarily on its chicken business. 

</P>
<P>
 *Avon Products Inc., down 9 7/8 at 25 13/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Avon said fourth-quarter earnings are likely to miss analysts'  
estimates due to falling currencies in Brazil and Mexico. The 
company, a direct seller of cosmetics, gets two-thirds of its 
profit outside the United States. 

</P>
<P>
 *Abbott Laboratories, down 2 1/2 at 37 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	The U.S. Food and Drug Administration told Abbott it is out of  
compliance with government quality-assurance regulations at a plant 
that makes chemical kits used in much of the company's 
medical-diagnostic equipment. 

</P>
<P>
 *Kranzco Realty Trust, down 2 1/4 at 9 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	Kranzco, a real estate investment trust, cut its dividend by 32  
percent and revealed it was in talks with third parties about 
strategic alternatives. The dividend cut was not unexpected, as 
Kranzco had been selling assets in recent months to raise cash. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Amazon.com, up 14 7/8 at 80 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	Amazon.com announced a plan to allow anyone -- from major  
manufacturers to creative housewives -- to sell merchandise through 
its Web site. The company's new zSHOPS program is expected to 
further its goal of becoming an online superstore. 

</P>
<P>
 *Insurance Management Solutions Group Inc., down 2 at 3 3/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The St. Petersburg, Fla., provider of policy and claims services  
to casualty insurance companies, said it expects to just break even 
in the third quarter. The company also expects net income for its 
fourth quarter to miss previous estimates. 

</P>
<P>
 *ITXC Corp., up 4 at 32 1/4    	
</P>
<P>
	ITXC continued to rise in its second day of trading following  
its initial public offering. ITXC provides Internet-based voice and 
fax services. 

</P>
<P>
 *Foundry Networks Inc., down 26 1/4 at 130    	
</P>
<P>
	Investors sold stock to capture profits after Foundry's initial  
public offering on Tuesday. In one of the best-performing recent 
IPOs, Foundry shares opened at 109 after being priced at 25 each. 
Foundry makes computer networking products. 



  	   	
