<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Accident Sidelines Rangers' Munoz </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) -- The Texas Rangers' highly rated bullpen  
received a scare on Wednesday when left-hander Mike Munoz broke his 
right foot in an accident at home. 
</P>
<P>
	Munoz dropped a computer monitor on his foot Wednesday  
afternoon. X-rays revealed the fracture, but the Rangers think 
Munoz will be available for the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
	The Rangers said Munoz will return to the bullpen after he is  
fitted with a protective plate in his right shoe. Team orthopedic 
consultant Dr. John Conway examined him on Wednesday night and 
found no further complications. 
</P>
<P>
	Texas has had only two left-handers in its bullpen most of the  
season -- Munoz and Mike Venafro. Munoz had allowed only one run in 
his previous nine outings and is 1-0 with a 2.40 ERA in his last 17 
appearances. 
</P>
<P>
	Rangers relievers have combined for 30 victories and a  
club-record 47 saves this season. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
