<HEADLINE> Players Laud Bonds, Griffey, Maddux </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Barry Bonds, Ken Griffey Jr. and Greg Maddux  
were selected Wednesday as the finalists for player of the decade 
in voting by their colleagues. 
</P>
<P>
	Boston's Pedro Martinez was selected the American League's  
Outstanding Pitcher in the Players' Choice awards, and was the lone 
finalist for the category. He has won or shared an outstanding 
pitcher award for three straight years. 
</P>
<P>
	Martinez, Rafael Palmeiro and Sammy Sosa were selected as  
finalists for player of the year. Cal Ripken, Sosa and Matt 
Williams were picked as finalists for the Man of the Year award, 
given to players for on-field performance and contributions to 
their community. 
</P>
<P>
	In the AL, Roberto Alomar, Palmeiro and Manny Ramirez are the  
finalists for outstanding player; Carlos Beltran, Freddy Garcia and 
Jeff Zimmerman for outstanding rookie; and John Jaha, Luis Polonia 
and Randy Velarde for comeback player. 
</P>
<P>
	In the NL, Jeff Bagwell, Chipper Jones and Sosa are finalists  
for outstanding player; Mike Hampton, Randy Johnson and Jose Lima 
for outstanding pitcher; Warren Morris, Scott Williamson and 
Preston Wilson for outstanding rookie; and Kent Bottenfield, Alex 
Fernandez and Rickey Henderson for comeback player. 
</P>
<P>
	The voting was conducted this month by the Major League Players  
Association. Winners will be announced Nov. 5. 
</P>
