<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Nabisco To Acquire Candy Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARSIPPANY, N.J. (AP) -- Nabisco Holdings Corp. plans to acquire  
troubled candymaker Favorite Brands International Inc. for $475 
million, company officials said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Bannockburn, Ill-based Favorite Brands is the nation's fourth  
largest non-chocolate candy company, with annual sales of $700 
million, but is currently reorganizing under Chapter 11 bankruptcy 
protection. 
</P>
<P>
	Nabisco hopes to close on the deal in the fourth quarter, said  
Henry Sandbach, a company spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
	Favorite Brands is the largest manufacturer of marshmallow  
products, including Jet-Puffed and private label brands, and the 
second-largest producer of gummy candy in the United States. 
</P>
<P>
	Nabisco's most recent acquisition took place on Sept. 9, when it  
purchased Canale of Argentina, a producer of biscuits and other 
food products with sales of $100 million. 
</P>
<P>
	In June, Nabisco reported a decline in its operating profits for  
the second quarter to $231 million, compared with $253 million a 
year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
	Parsippany, N.J.-based Nabisco produces such brands as Oreo  
cookies, Ritz crackers, Planters nuts and A.1. steak sauces. The 
company markets its products in the United States, Canada and more 
than 85 other countries worldwide. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
