<HEADLINE> Leafs Sign Berard to Two-Year Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TORONTO (AP) -- The Toronto Maple Leafs re-signed Bryan Berard to  
a two-year contract on Wednesday, ending an offseason impasse that 
had kept Berard and fellow defenseman Dimitri Yushkevich off the 
ice. 
</P>
<P>
	The contract will pay Berard, 22, a reported $3.3 million over  
the two years, $1.5 million this year and $1.8 million in the 
second year. 
</P>
<P>
	Berard and Yushkevich were no-shows for training camp while  
their contracts were being negotiated. 
</P>
<P>
	Yushkevich, Toronto's best defender last season, remained  
unsigned three days before the Leafs open the season at Montreal. 
</P>
<P>
	The Leafs acquired Berard from the New York Islanders in  
January. He had five goals and 14 assists for the Leafs, adding a 
goal and eight assists during the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
	Berard was the first overall draft pick in 1995 by the Ottawa  
Senators and was selected rookie of the year in 1997 with the 
Islanders, with eight goals and 40 assists in 82 games. 
  	   	
