<HEADLINE> NPS Pharmaceuticals To Buy Allelix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- NPS Pharmaceuticals announced that it  
plans to acquire the Canadian company Allelix Biopharmaceuticals in 
a stock deal valued at $45.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
	NPS will issue about 6.5 million shares of stock to Allelix  
shareholders, exchanging 0.3238 of an NPS share for each Allelix 
stock. 
</P>
<P>
	The company will operate as NPS Pharmaceuticals in the United  
States and as NPS Allelix in Canada. 
</P>
<P>
	Both firms have been exploring treatments for osteoporosis and  
central nervous system disorders. 
</P>
<P>
	Following the announcement Tuesday, shares in NPS fell $1,  
closing at $6 on trading of 65,600 shares. 
</P>
<P>
	NPS said it will cut more than 35 positions from its 100-member  
work force in Salt Lake City. Allelix, which recently cuts its 
staff by 50 percent, has about 115 employees in Toronto and New 
Jersey. 
</P>
<P>
	Last month, NPS reported a net loss of nearly $10.8 million for  
the first six months of this year, with revenue of $1.8 million. 
</P>
<P>
	The acquisition is subject to the approval of shareholders in  
both companies and Canadian judicial review. It is expected to 
close in the first quarter of 2000. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
