<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ralph Fiennes Returning to Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Ralph Fiennes will return to the London stage next  
spring in the title roles of Shakespeare's ``Richard II'' and 
``Coriolanus.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Almeida Theater productions open April 12 and June 14 at  
Gainsborough Studios, possibly followed by a New York appearance. 
</P>
<P>
	Fiennes, 36, won a Tony Award for best actor in the 1995  
Broadway performance of ``Hamlet.'' 
</P>
<P>
	He appears in several new films, including an adaptation of  
Graham Greene's ``The End of the Affair'' and ``Onegin,'' directed 
by the actor's sister, Martha. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
